sentences.english: Dvorak was interested in the folk music of both Europe and North America.

sentences.english: Senecio jacobaea L. is found in Xinjiang province of China also in North America.

sentences.english: New World curlew that breeds in northern North America.

sentences.english: West Nile virus first appeared in North America in 1999.
sentences.chinese: 西尼羅河病毒最早是1999年在北美洲被發現的。

sentences.english: North American lemming having a white winter coat and some claws much enlarged.

sentences.english: Highlights included going to the utterly fantastic U'mista Cultural Center, absolutely the finest museum of native Canadian (or American) artifacts I have ever seen.

sentences.english: Would someone help me locate a dealer for I-Go north america maps?

sentences.english: But the tide is turning, even in North America.
sentences.chinese: 但是即便是在北美洲，趨勢也正在改變。

sentences.english: But only until the land in North America brings itself back into equilibrium.
sentences.chinese: 但那也要等到北美洲的島嶼全部平衡了纔會那樣啊。

sentences.english: Il Canada si trova nell'America del nord.
The first set of assessments in North America took place in Toronto at IAF Conference 2000.
sentences.chinese: 第一次北美洲的認證在2000年多倫多舉行。

sentences.english: Lunenburg is the best surviving example of a planned British colonial settlement in North America.
sentences.chinese: 盧嫩堡是北美洲設計精心的英國殖民據點的典範。

sentences.english: North American freshwater bass resembling the larger marine striped bass.

sentences.english: North American orchid having a solitary leaf and flowers with threadlike petals.
